 graph of an inequality\" class=\"sr-only\"><ul>\n<li>The boundary of the inequality is a solid line.\n<ul>\n<li>The line is horizontal.</li>\n<li>The line passes through the following points:\n<ul>\n<li>(negative 15 comma 36)</li>\n<li>(0 comma 36)</li>\n<li>(15 comma 36)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The area above the boundary is shaded.</li>\n</ul></div></figure></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The shaded region shown in the graph represents all the solutions to which inequality?</p>",
